quran[12]{c,v,t}:
  7,130,"Certainly We afflicted Pharaoh’s clan with droughts and loss of produce, so that they may take admonition"
  7,131,"But whenever any good came to them, they would say, ‘This is our due.’ And if any ill visited them, they took it for ill omens attending Moses and those who were with him. (Look! Indeed the cause of their ill omens is from Allah, but most of them do not know)"
  7,132,"And they said, ‘Whatever sign you may bring us to bewitch us, we are not going to believe you.’"
  7,133,"So We sent against them a flood and locusts, lice, frogs and blood, as distinct signs. But they acted arrogantly, and they were a guilty lot"
  7,134,"Whenever a plague fell upon them, they would say, ‘O Moses, invoke your Lord for us by the covenant He has made with you. If you remove the plague from us, we will certainly believe in you and let the Children of Israel go along with you.’"
  7,135,"But when We had removed the plague from them until a term that they should have completed, behold, they broke their promise"
  7,136,"So We took vengeance on them and drowned them in the sea, for they denied Our signs and were oblivious to them"
  7,137,"We made the people who were abased the heirs to the east and west of the land which We had blessed, and your Lord’s best word [of promise] was fulfilled for the Children of Israel because of their patience, and We destroyed what Pharaoh and his people had built and what they used to erect"
  7,138,"We carried the Children of Israel across the sea, whereat they came upon a people cleaving to certain idols that they had. They said, ‘O Moses, make for us a god like the gods that they have.’ He said, ‘You are indeed an ignorant lot"
  7,139,"What they are engaged in is indeed bound to perish, and what they have been doing shall come to naught.’"
  7,140,"He said, ‘Shall I find you a god other than Allah, while He has graced you over all the nations?’"
  7,141,"And when We delivered you from Pharaoh’s clan who inflicted on you a terrible torment, slaughtering your sons and sparing your women, and there was a great test in that from your Lord"